snippet.textDisplay:
To everyone who finds it odd that they drove around three countries for a bit of chocolate milk.

I live 10 miles away from the Slovenian and Italian border in Austria. On my way to the UK we visited my granny who lives at the border to Slovenia and then my parents dropped me off in Italy from where I took the train to Venice where I fly from. From home to Slovenia and then Italy it takes about 30 minutes. It's quite normal for us to go shopping in Slovenia and then go for dinner in Italy.

snippet.textDisplay: Brits like the Germana have a good talent for building very good cars. Where the Germans score over the Brits is they sell more of their cars worldwide.  Because they mass produce it in very efficient factory conditions at a quicker rate and build it more economically so they can sell it worldwide customers that is good cars at competitive prices. There is a reason the Germans have a good economy I suggest this is one of the reasona. The Brits like the Germans make good cars but they don't mass produce them or sell them at more competitive rates than their German counterparts. The German cars as a result has become popular worldwide with lower middle class and middle class customers.
